  "text": "A standard treatment for muscle-invasive bladder cancer (MIBC) remains radical cystectomy with pelvic lymph node dissection, with a 50 % 5-year overall survival rate for cT2-4 tumors in contemporary large series [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
